01,202,201,202,92,203,95],"isic001126","i.sicily inscription 001126",{"_":5},"sicilia","sicily","ancient greek",[],{"title":206,"body":207,"divs":208,"editions":233,"images":243,"handnote":244},"ISic001126. I.Sicily inscription 001126","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διόγενες\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διόγενες\">[Διό?]γενε[ς\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΛΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[χρησ]τὲ καὶ ἄ̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[μεμ]πτε χαῖ[ρ]ε̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ἔζησε̣ ἔ̣τη̣ [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] ΑΚΓΑΜΠϹ [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] ΛΙΝ μήτηρ [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al7-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] ἐποί&lt;η&gt;σε [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διόγενες\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διόγενες\">[...]ΓΕΝΕ[.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΛΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[....]ΤΕΚΑΙ.\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[...]ΠΤΕΧΑΙ[.].\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΕΖΗΣ..Τ.[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΑΚΓΑΜΠϹ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΛΙΝΜΗΤΗΡ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al7-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΕΠΟΙΣΕ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based upon Torremuzza, with considerable uncertainty about the extent of the lacunae; similar restoration in Kaibel\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Diogenes(?) [...] worthy and blameless, lived [...] years [...] his mother set this up [...]\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>A funerary inscription with probably a Greek name such as Diogenes (plus filiation?) in the first line, the typical Sicilian formula 'chrestos kai amemptos' in lines 2-3, age at death in years, and then reference to erection of the inscription by the deceased's mother. As Kaibel notes, the gaps would appear to be small, and the implication is that the gaps at the start of the line are of variable length, as well as at line end. The 'chrestos kai amemptos' formula is distinctively Sicilian, but primarily attested in Syracusae and Catina (from Palermo, compare \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001119\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001119\u003C/a>, which however, like this text, is not explicitly attested as being found in Palermo. In both cases therefore, an eastern Sicilian provenance cannot be ruled out.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Castelli 1762 53 no.103 and p.374 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002085\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002085\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 cl.18 no.30 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 cl. 18 no.30 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5575 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">307\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Torremuzza is explicit that the text includes a quadrate lunate sigma and square omicron.\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[209,212,215,218,221,224,227,230],{"id":210,"html":211},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διόγενες\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διόγενες\">[Διό?]γενε[ς\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΛΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[χρησ]τὲ καὶ ἄ̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[μεμ]πτε χαῖ[ρ]ε̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ἔζησε̣ ἔ̣τη̣ [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] ΑΚΓΑΜΠϹ [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] ΛΙΝ μήτηρ [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al7-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] ἐποί&lt;η&gt;σε [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διόγενες\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διόγενες\">[...]ΓΕΝΕ[.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΛΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[....]ΤΕΚΑΙ.\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[...]ΠΤΕΧΑΙ[.].\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΕΖΗΣ..Τ.[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΑΚΓΑΜΠϹ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΛΙΝΜΗΤΗΡ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al7-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΕΠΟΙΣΕ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":213,"html":214},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>",{"id":216,"html":217},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based upon Torremuzza, with considerable uncertainty about the extent of the lacunae; similar restoration in Kaibel\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":219,"html":220},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Diogenes(?) [...] worthy and blameless, lived [...] years [...] his mother set this up [...]\u003C/p>  ",{"id":222,"html":223},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>A funerary inscription with probably a Greek name such as Diogenes (plus filiation?) in the first line, the typical Sicilian formula 'chrestos kai amemptos' in lines 2-3, age at death in years, and then reference to erection of the inscription by the deceased's mother. As Kaibel notes, the gaps would appear to be small, and the implication is that the gaps at the start of the line are of variable length, as well as at line end. The 'chrestos kai amemptos' formula is distinctively Sicilian, but primarily attested in Syracusae and Catina (from Palermo, compare \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001119\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001119\u003C/a>, which however, like this text, is not explicitly attested as being found in Palermo. In both cases therefore, an eastern Sicilian provenance cannot be ruled out.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":225,"html":226},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Castelli 1762 53 no.103 and p.374 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002085\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002085\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 cl.18 no.30 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 cl. 18 no.30 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5575 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">307\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":228,"html":229},"handnote","\u003Cp>Torremuzza is explicit that the text includes a quadrate lunate sigma and square omicron.\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":231,"html":232},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[234,236,239,240],{"html":235},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":237,"lang":95,"html":238},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διόγενες\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διόγενες\">[Διό?]γενε[ς\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΛΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[χρησ]τὲ καὶ ἄ̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[μεμ]πτε χαῖ[ρ]ε̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ἔζησε̣ ἔ̣τη̣ [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan 